title: Nill Battey Sannata
subTitle: When Apeksha loses her interest in academics, her mother Chanda joins school to complete her education and motivate Apeksha.

title: The Last Color
subTitle: Choti, a young tightrope walker, wishes to pursue her education but struggles to make a living. She soon befriends Noor, a widow who yearns to play Holi but is forced to live a life of abstinence.

title: U-Turn
subTitle: Rachana, an intern at a newspaper, investigates accidents occurring on a flyover with the help of a crime reporter. However, the situation changes when she is accused of murder.

title: Sonchiriya
subTitle: After their leader's death, a group of dacoits splits up and runs away. On the way, they meet two women and help them escape their family and reach the hospital.

title: Madaari
subTitle: Nirmal, a man who lost his son due to the negligence of the government, seeks revenge and kidnaps the ten-year-old son of the home minister, forcing the administration to meet his demands.

title: Go Goa Gone
subTitle: Things take a dangerous turn when the aftermath of a rave party causes three friends to get stranded on an isolated island infested with zombies.

title: Gold
subTitle: Tapan Das, a passionate team manager with a penchant for alcohol, embarks a ragtag group of hockey players on an ambitious quest for independent India's first Olympic gold medal.

title: Madgaon Express
subTitle: Childhood friends Dodo, Ayush, and Pinku embark on a trip to Goa that goes completely off-track due to a sequence of terrible decisions.

title: Raangi
subTitle: Thaiyal Nayagi tries to protect her niece from an online predator. However, things escalate when the FBI's attempt to catch the culprit puts them both in danger as they unwittingly become bait.

title: Hamari Adhuri Kahani
subTitle: Half a decade after her husband went missing, Vasudha, a single mother, falls for Aarav, a hotelier. However, her missing husband, Hari, returns, thereby creating a rift between the two lovers.

title: Jersey
subTitle: Arjun, a talented but failed cricketer, decides to return to cricket in his late thirties driven by the desire to represent the Indian cricket team and fulfil his son's wish for a jersey as a gift.

title: Hotel Mumbai
subTitle: A hotel staff risks everything to keep its patrons safe during a terror attack, especially a British heiress, her husband and her infant.

title: Hotel Mumbai
subTitle: A hotel staff risks everything to keep its patrons safe during a terror attack, especially a British heiress, her husband and her infant.

title: CityLights
subTitle: Deepak Singh, an ex-army person from Rajasthan, moves to Mumbai with his family hoping for a better lifestyle. However, upon arrival, he realises that everything is not as easy as it seems.

title: Chakravyuh
subTitle: Kabir infiltrates a Maoist organisation to help Adil Khan, who is a decorated police officer and his friend. As he gets deeper into the organisation, Kabir starts sympathising with the group's plight and starts having second thoughts.

title: Silence-Can You Hear It?
subTitle: A seasoned narcotics officer is recruited for a special task force. Subsequently, he uncovers shocking truths while investigating a high-profile murder.

title: India Lockdown
subTitle: The lives of four individuals - a father, his pilot daughter, a prostitute, and a migrant worker - are thrown into turmoil when the Indian government announces a nationwide lockdown.

title: Kanjoos Makkichoos
subTitle: Jamnaprasad Pandey intends to send his parents on a pilgrimage. However, things take a devastating turn when they disappear during a flood.

title: Love Hostel
subTitle: A series of bloodshed, escapes and deception ensue when Jyothi and Ashu elope together and her family hires a ruthless mercenary to kill the couple.

title: Uri: The Surgical Strike
subTitle: Major Vihaan Singh Shergill of the Indian Army leads a covert operation against a group of militants who attacked a base in Uri, Kashmir, in 2016 and killed many soldiers.

title: Auron Mein Kahan Dum Tha
subTitle: As Krishna, an incarcerated man, faces early release, his love story with Vasudha from more than twenty years ago unfurls.

title: Chhatriwali
subTitle: While struggling to find work, Sanya accepts a unique job and ends up leading a quiet revolution in how her community thinks about health and responsibility.

title: Parmanu: The Story of Pokhran
subTitle: A team of Indian government officials must manoeuvre a high-stakes nuclear test in a town in Rajasthan without being detected by reconnaissance satellites or espionage networks.

title: Khaali Peeli
subTitle: Torn apart as young lovers, Pooja and Blackie's lives take different paths. Fate brings them back together after Pooja's courageous escape from a brothel.

title: Khaali Peeli
subTitle: Torn apart as young lovers, Pooja and Blackie's lives take different paths. Fate brings them back together after Pooja's courageous escape from a brothel.

title: Mere Pyare Prime Minister
subTitle: After his mother is raped one night, Kannu, an eight-year-old boy, writes a letter to the prime minister of India and embarks on a journey from Mumbai to Delhi with his two friends.

title: Daas Dev
subTitle: Dev is the heir to the throne who is challenged by his beloved Paro in his political backyard. Chandni loves Dev, although she knows that her love is unrequited.

title: Lost
subTitle: A journalist relentlessly investigates to uncover the truth behind the sudden and mysterious disappearance of a young activist.

title: Footfairy
subTitle: A CBI officer investigates a string of gruesome murders committed by a serial killer with a foot festish. However, things take an ugly turn when he gets close to catching the killer.

title: Faraaz
subTitle: Five terrorists take the staff and customers of Holey Artisan cafe in Dhaka hostage. Faraaz and his friends are among the hostages as the police try to de-escalate the situation.

title: Mom
subTitle: Devki, a biology teacher, seeks help from DK, a private detective, and vows to get revenge after her stepdaughter's rapists are acquitted by the court.

title: Tejas
subTitle: A brave Indian pilot sets on a mission to rescue a spy from Pakistan who holds confidential information and faces her inner fears from the past.

title: Firaaq
subTitle: In the aftermath of Gujarat's violent 2002 riots, victims find their lives changed forever and reel from the deep impact the upheaval left on them.

title: Kismat Konnection
subTitle: Raj, an out-of-luck architect, and Priya, an out-of-love social activist, find themselves connected in a strange way by destiny.

title: Raanjhanaa
subTitle: A carefree youngster sacrifices his love after his childhood sweetheart plans to marry a man from her own community. Nevertheless, fate convinces him to pursue his lady love at any cost.

title: Blurr
subTitle: Suspicious about the circumstances surrounding her twin sister's death, a woman with progressive blindness searches for answers that eventually lead her down a dangerous path.
